    "Knowing that there is only one person-Abigailin his household fully capable of making the exact kind of coffee he prefers, with knowledge of where he customarily sits, Bertram abduces via I A, instantiated, to produce the following argument, to which Bertram accedes, and the mystery is solved (and he has gained knowledge as to whence the coffee cup).",
    "OnTable(cup22) 2.",
    "Prepared(abigail,cup22) → OnTable(cup22) ∴ 3.",
    "Prepared(abigail, cup22)",
    "Unfortunately, as has been long and widely appreciated, I A, and indeed any schema that is of this general sort, is deeply problematic."
